â€œThis I have gained today, and that longing I will fulfil. This wealth is mine, and that also shall be mine in future;
â€œThat enemy I have slain, and others, too, I will slay. I am the lord of all; I enjoy; I am prosperous, mighty, and happy;
â€œI am rich; I am of high birth. Who else is equal to me? I will offer sacrifice, I will give, I will rejoice.â€ Thus, deluded by ignorance,
Bewildered by many fancies, entangled in the meshes of delusion, addicted to the gratification of lust, they fall into a loathsome hell.

